This paper deals with the analysis of networks, specifically signed bipartite networks, which can be categorized under social networks (cs.SOC) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of balance theory and sign prediction methods also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing literature, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
